every sounding Wood With good Eliza's Name to ring around
the solemn Day they find , When young Albino
sweet the Rose ! how speedy the Decay
sweet the Rose ! how speedy the Decay
sympathising Rocks in Echo groaned , Presaging future Woe

he lay , His beauteous Limbs upon the dampy Clay , The Roses on his pallid Cheeks decayed , And over his lips a livid Hue displayed : Bleating around him lie his pensive Sheep , And mourning Shepherd's come in Crouds to weep , The pious Mother comes , with Grief oppressed : You , conscious Trees and Fountains , can attest With what sad Accents and what moving Cries She filled the Grove , and importuned the Skies , And every Star upbraided with his Death , When in her widowed Arms , devoid of Breath , She clasped her Son
what sad Accents and what moving Cries She filled the Grove

the peaceful Empire of the Field
Who now shall teach the pointed Spear to
to bless thy Mother's Days , To share the sacred Honours of her praise
thy Mother's Days , To share the sacred Honours of her praise

! if ever , bring The Laurel green , the smelling Eglantine , And tender Branches from the mantling Vine , The dewy Cowslip , that in Meadow grows , The Fountain Violet and the Garden Rose : Your Hamlets strew , and every public Way , And consecrate to Mirth Albino's Day
The Fountain Violet and the Garden
